The internet is like a drug, you can't tell everyone to just do a little bit of it. The convenience, the noise, the overstimulation is all part of it and how people consume anthro material is directly tied to it. I can draw anthro ladies all day or write a story about them by myself but it will only leave me wanting more, it doesn't produce tangible results other than something to look at and imagine. Loving and dreaming about anthro women is inherently self-draining because they're not real. You're expending more energy than you're getting. Hmofa works because we know we're getting validation from other autists with the same problem, it gets more interesting. At least we know there are real people here, its also the only place we know of where people discuss this very very specific thing.
